I am wondering whether the validate routine was originally intended to receive a list (but misbehaved when passed a string). The new version doesn't validate bits defaults, which cause a list to be passed. The following seems to work.

```python
    def validate(self, errors, pos, val, errstr = ''):
        if type(val) == list:
            for v in val:
                if util.keysearch(v, 0, self.bits) == None:
                    err_add(errors, pos, 'TYPE_VALUE',
                            (v, self.definition, 'bit not defined' + errstr))
                    return False
        else:
            if util.keysearch(val, 0, self.bits) == None:
                err_add(errors, pos, 'TYPE_VALUE',
                        (val, self.definition, 'bit not defined' + errstr))
                return False
        return True
```

