After reading [here](http://jsonapi.org/format/#document-resource-object-relationships), [here](http://jsonapi.org/format/#document-resource-object-linkage) and glancing at the [JSON Schema](http://jsonapi.org/schema) again, it appears that the following is valid:

```JSON
"relationships": {
    "parent": {
        "data": null
    }
}
```

because `/relationships/parent/data` is a [resource linkage](http://jsonapi.org/format/#document-resource-object-linkage), and resource linkages may be `null`.

However, this is invalid:

```JSON
"relationships": {
    "parent": null
}
```

So it seems that the correct way to serialize null relationships is to have a `null` resource linkage. I'm not sure what the behavior should be for a null relationship if `include_data=False`. I suppose we could serialize to `missing` so that the relationship object would be non-existent.

